Foreign Investors Increase Holdings of Greek Stocks in February

-- B y   E l e n i   C h r e p a
-- 
2011-03-09T13:55:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/foreign-investors-increase-holdings-of-greek-stocks-in-february.html
Foreign investors raised their share
of stocks listed on the Greek stock exchange during February,
according to data released by the country’s Central Securities
Depository today.  Non-resident investors held 51.2 percent of the market
value of all stocks listed on the Athens Stock Exchange in
February, up from 49 percent in February 2010. In the first
month of the year, foreign investors owned 51.6 percent,
according to figures released Feb. 7.    Greece ’s benchmark ASE lost 5.2 percent in February and has
gained 9.5 percent so far this year. Foreign investors accounted
for 45 percent of total turnover in February, according to
today’s statement.  To contact the reporter on this story: Eleni Chrepa in Athens
   echrepa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: Angela Cullen
at   acullen@bloomberg.net  